Baseline Risk Analysis for Burkina Faso

By Centre for Humanitarian Data

2021-03-24

This is an initial exploration into humanitarian risks and vulnerabilities in Burkina Faso. Data is compiled and presented on the following elements:

  • Flooding risk
  • Drought risk
  • Population
  • Internally displaced persons
  • Food security
  • Poverty
  • Operational presence
  • Seasonal precipitation forecast

These factors vary across regions as shown by the figure below.

Geographic overview of key factors

The North-Eastern regions of Burkina Faso (eg. Sahel, Centre-Nord) are more vulnerable, with high flood and drought risk. These regions also have a population more vulnerable to food insecurity and larger number of IDPs relative to the rest of the country. The countrys humanitarian presence is also most focused on these regions.

Vulnerable populations facing high hazard risk

We see a greater total population in regions facing high flooding risk. By this factor alone, we could perhaps estimate that flooding would have a larger humanitarian impact.
